The number of newly diagnosed patients in Wuhan increased by 13,000 in a single day.

In accordance with the classification of cases published in other provinces of China, Hubei Province has included the number of clinically diagnosed cases into the number of confirmed cases to be published from February 12.

This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Cui Huiying and Ma Suping, southern weekend journalists

Editor in chief | Cao Haidong

In one day, there were 14,840 new cases of pneumonia in Hubei.

In the early morning of February 13,2020, the number of confirmed cases was so high that many people suspected that they were "dazed" .

The number of clinically diagnosed cases will be included in the number of confirmed cases to be announced from the same day, according to the Health Commission of Hubei Province. That is to say, the change of statistical caliber, 13332 cases of clinical diagnosis were included, is the main reason for the sharp increase in the number of confirmed patients.

1
Doctors urge that CT images be included in diagnostic criteria

1

###Doctors urge that CT images be included in diagnostic criteria

Ten days earlier, front line doctors had aggressively scanned CT images for a new diagnosis of pneumonia, which was all over the Internet. On the morning of February 4, Zhang Xiaochun, deputy director of the Medical Imaging Department of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, which sent out the "exploding money" message, told southern weekend that there would be many missed diagnoses based on nucleic acid test results alone. "You may have to cough up a lot of sputum to be positive, but the quality of the sputum is not very good, and the quality of the test kit itself may also affect the test results, with the possibility of a false negative. "

Zhang Xiaochun suggested that CT images should be used as diagnostic criteria in Hubei Province where the epidemic situation is serious. Patients who have seen images of "white lung" but have not been tested for nucleic acid reagents should be isolated as soon as possible. "because there is no specific drug, the clinical treatment of common acute pneumonia is the same as that of new coronary pneumonia in our key epidemic areas, and there is no specific differential diagnosis reported, " Zhang said.

In accordance with current guidelines, the gold standard for detection of COVID-19 by real time RT-PCR was positive. The reality is that, from the beginning of the outbreak of new pneumonia, in Hubei Province, where the epidemic is severe, the problem of the shortage of reagent kits and the difficulty of obtaining the diagnosis result need some time, and has not been solved properly.

Peng Zhiyong, director of the Department of Critical Care Medicine at Wuhan University's Zhongnan Hospital, also told southern weekend that front-line doctors had proposed to include CT images in the diagnostic criteria in January 2020, but had not been given a "clear name. ".

The change came on February 5, when the National Health and COVID-19's latest release, the Fifth Edition, incorporated CT findings into clinical diagnostic criteria for new suspected cases of pneumonia, limited to Hubei.

In other words, suspected cases in Hubei Province, if the imaging features of pneumonia, can be included in the number of confirmed cases.

2
Hubei and the national level, the clinical diagnosis case includes the confirmed case

2

###Hubei and the national level, the clinical diagnosis case includes the confirmed case

On Feb. 8, Jiang Chaoliang, then the party secretary of Hubei Province, oversaw the epidemic in Wuhan, saying that all suspected cases in the city would be tested within two days.

Changes can also be seen in the data, which show a sharp drop in the number of suspected cases reported daily in Hubei Province since February 8, when the province began to publish its inventory of suspected cases. From February 8 to 12, the number of suspected cases were 23638,18438,16687,11295 and 9028 respectively.

But between February 8 and 12, the number of confirmed cases in Hubei Province did not increase significantly. On February 11, Hubei Province reported only 1,638 new cases of coronary pneumonia.

The same is true in Wuhan, where 13,436 cases of NCP were reported in Wuhan on February 12, up from 1,104 the previous day.

On February 13, Hubei Province recently screened suspected cases and revised the diagnosis, according to the Hubei Health Commission's website, and new patients were diagnosed according to the new diagnostic classification. In accordance with the classification of cases published in other provinces of China, Hubei Province has included the number of clinically diagnosed cases into the number of confirmed cases to be published from February 12.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It is noteworthy that the newly admitted confirmed cases are mainly concentrated in Wuhan. Wuhan has 13,436 new confirmed cases, including 12,364 clinically diagnosed cases.

For the severe epidemic in Wuhan, it is the first step for the patients to receive standard treatment according to the confirmed cases, further improve the success rate of treatment, clear standards, figure out the bottom number.
